WEBVTT

00:00.835 --> 00:02.301
♪ ♪

00:02.386 --> 00:04.336
hey, grandma!
What you reading?

00:04.472 --> 00:06.388
A book of french poetry.

00:06.474 --> 00:07.506
Really? Is it good?

00:07.641 --> 00:09.925
I don't know. It's in french.

00:12.179 --> 00:14.680
Hey, where's dad?
I wanna ask him
if I can redo my room.

00:14.815 --> 00:17.549
Ooh, that's a tough one.
You know how sentimental he is.

00:17.651 --> 00:20.269
Yeah, but I changed over summer.
Maybe he did, too.

00:20.354 --> 00:22.771
Syd, I can't believe
you threw out

00:22.857 --> 00:24.490
your empty
sunblock from camp!

00:24.575 --> 00:27.192
This baby's going
right in the scrapbook.

00:27.862 --> 00:29.328
-Oh boy.
-Oh boy.

00:31.415 --> 00:34.366
Well, I'm off to<i> le parc</i>
with my baguette.

00:34.502 --> 00:37.453
You know, it's the only bread
that's also a back-scratcher.

00:41.592 --> 00:43.842
Dad, I need to talk to you
about something important.

00:43.928 --> 00:45.127
Shoot.

00:45.880 --> 00:47.079
I wanna redo my room.

00:47.181 --> 00:48.714
And I know what
you're gonna say.

00:48.849 --> 00:51.350
(imitating):
"but, syd, that room
has so many memories."

00:51.435 --> 00:53.719
yes, but changing it
won't take them away.

00:53.854 --> 00:55.521
"sounds kinda pricey."

00:55.606 --> 00:58.524
it won't be 'cause I'm selling
my old furniture to pay for it.

00:58.642 --> 01:01.393
"but I don't have time for
a big project right now."

01:01.479 --> 01:03.395
I promise you won't
lift a finger.

01:04.365 --> 01:06.231
Am I done?

01:06.951 --> 01:08.067
You are.

01:08.202 --> 01:10.152
Fine, you can
redo your room.

01:11.205 --> 01:12.204
Seriously?

01:12.289 --> 01:14.656
Yeah! You grew up
a lot this summer.

01:14.742 --> 01:16.458
It's your room, syd.
Make it yours.

01:16.994 --> 01:19.661
Thanks, dad! Well,
I better go start on my redo!

01:19.747 --> 01:22.581
Now? I thought you might
finally tell me about camp.

01:23.834 --> 01:26.218
Trees, music, bonfires.
Gotta go!

01:26.720 --> 01:28.754
Wow. It's like I was there.

01:29.640 --> 01:31.840
♪ ♪

01:31.926 --> 01:33.092
can you believe it, leo?

01:33.227 --> 01:35.844
-Our first day as 8th graders.
-I was so excited,

01:35.930 --> 01:37.563
I barely slept last night.

01:37.648 --> 01:40.099
But when you look this good,
it's hard to tell.

01:42.269 --> 01:44.570
-Now we're the big men
on campus.
-Yep.

01:44.655 --> 01:47.272
-Walking tall.
-Everyone looking up to us.

01:52.746 --> 01:54.446
Am I imagining it,

01:54.582 --> 01:57.149
or did everyone have a growth
spurt this summer except me?

01:57.251 --> 01:59.251
So what? Who cares?

01:59.336 --> 02:01.870
Hey, leo. Hey, shortstack.

02:03.507 --> 02:05.374
Okay, pete cares.

02:07.962 --> 02:11.296
Leo, I think I must be
the shortest kid in 8th grade.

02:11.432 --> 02:13.382
Dude, don't sweat it.

02:13.467 --> 02:14.850
If you're worried
about anything,

02:14.969 --> 02:16.334
it should be your grades.

02:16.437 --> 02:18.387
Hoo-doggy.

02:19.440 --> 02:21.023
Forget about your height, man.

02:21.142 --> 02:22.307
You're right. I will.

02:23.644 --> 02:26.145
Right after I find a way to
grow three inches by tomorrow.

02:26.814 --> 02:30.199
Dang. And it looked like you
were listening and everything.

02:30.317 --> 02:33.285
♪ ♪

02:36.490 --> 02:37.990
oh my gosh.

02:38.075 --> 02:39.958
I've never seen your
room naked before.

02:40.077 --> 02:42.995
Stop staring.
You're making her blush.

02:43.964 --> 02:45.714
I can't believe
we're doing this!

02:45.833 --> 02:47.332
Oh! But, no worries.
I'm all prepared.

02:47.468 --> 02:50.969
I have sketch pads, pencils,
and even masks for painting.

02:51.088 --> 02:52.638
These days, I've got plenty.

02:52.756 --> 02:54.840
Cloth, disposable,

02:54.975 --> 02:56.141
schnauzer.

02:57.478 --> 02:59.077
So what's the plan?

02:59.180 --> 03:01.146
The plan is...

03:01.282 --> 03:03.048
There is no plan.

03:04.018 --> 03:07.152
Ooh! The no-plan plan.
What a great plan.

03:07.254 --> 03:10.388
No. The no-plan plan
isn't a plan.

03:10.774 --> 03:12.941
Still sounds like
a plan to me.

03:13.994 --> 03:16.245
Olive, it's like they
taught us at camp.

03:16.363 --> 03:18.330
The key to creating
great music

03:18.415 --> 03:20.365
is to follow your instincts.

03:20.451 --> 03:22.367
So, I'm gonna go with my gut.

03:22.503 --> 03:24.369
Now, can you help me put up
these last few samples?

03:33.964 --> 03:36.548
So, what's your gut saying?

03:36.634 --> 03:37.849
It says...

03:37.935 --> 03:39.801
(scary voice):
I like all of them!

03:41.305 --> 03:44.439
Sorry, syd's scary gut,
but you can't do all of them.

03:44.558 --> 03:47.809
(normal):
Who says? Art is all
about taking risks.

03:49.196 --> 03:50.562
Like this.

03:58.906 --> 04:00.239
Now your turn!

04:00.908 --> 04:02.958
Me? Oh, no, I couldn't--

04:03.043 --> 04:04.493
(scary voice):
Do it.

04:12.253 --> 04:14.419
What a rush!

04:15.973 --> 04:18.590
-Oh no! I got paint on
your floor. I'll get a rag.
-(normal): Don't!

04:19.727 --> 04:21.426
I just got an idea.

04:22.062 --> 04:23.395
We'll paint the floors.

04:23.514 --> 04:25.764
Who says paint
is only for walls?

04:25.899 --> 04:27.733
Painters?

04:27.818 --> 04:29.401
Olive, I want this room

04:29.520 --> 04:32.187
to look different than
anything I've ever seen before.

04:32.273 --> 04:33.638
So throw out the rulebook

04:33.741 --> 04:36.191
and let your creative
tiger out of its cage.

04:36.660 --> 04:37.826
(meow)

04:37.945 --> 04:39.278
more tiger, less kitten.

04:39.413 --> 04:41.580
-(roar)
-now we're talking!

04:41.665 --> 04:44.750
♪ ♪

04:47.254 --> 04:50.205
syd, you just stepped
in fresh paint.

04:51.008 --> 04:53.875
No. I just stepped
in a fresh idea.

04:53.994 --> 04:56.878
♪

05:00.050 --> 05:00.932
(splat)

05:04.938 --> 05:06.305
what are you doing?

05:06.440 --> 05:08.774
Writing all my song
lyrics on the walls.

05:09.276 --> 05:12.694
"I'm leaving all
of my fears...

05:12.813 --> 05:13.812
Beh"?

05:14.865 --> 05:16.815
Yeah, I ran out of space.

05:18.452 --> 05:19.901
(spraying)

05:21.455 --> 05:22.904
olive, I am so sorry!

05:23.657 --> 05:25.123
About what?

05:26.994 --> 05:28.994
Hey, you missed a spot.

05:32.966 --> 05:34.166
Is it ready yet, syd?

05:34.301 --> 05:36.551
I've run out of excuses
to walk by your door.

05:36.637 --> 05:38.670
Even I don't believe me anymore.

05:40.424 --> 05:43.258
Sydney:
Okay, dad, you've been
patient. Come on in.

05:43.977 --> 05:46.845
Oh, goodie. I can't wait
to see what you've done!

05:47.815 --> 05:49.264
What have you done?

05:51.185 --> 05:53.852
(whispering):
I don't think he likes
it as much as we do.

05:53.987 --> 05:55.520
Max:
No, I don't!

05:55.656 --> 05:57.823
It's a mess! I can't even
tell the walls from the floor!

05:57.941 --> 06:00.325
Oh my gosh,
you painted the floor.

06:00.411 --> 06:02.694
-And where's your desk?
-There.

06:02.780 --> 06:04.913
Oh, so you haven't
gotten one yet.

06:05.032 --> 06:06.531
No, that is the desk.

06:06.667 --> 06:08.750
It's called
deconstructivism.

06:08.836 --> 06:11.370
It's a kind of design
where you superimpose--

06:11.505 --> 06:13.872
yeah, I didn't
get it either.

06:13.957 --> 06:15.707
Well, I've got a new
kind of design for you.

06:15.843 --> 06:17.676
It's called reconstructivism.

06:17.761 --> 06:19.711
It means you're
redoing this room.

06:20.347 --> 06:22.381
What? No!

06:22.516 --> 06:23.932
This room is new syd.

06:24.051 --> 06:27.018
But how are you gonna
hang out in here?
Do homework?

06:27.137 --> 06:29.471
Not have nightmares?

06:30.140 --> 06:31.857
Well, I'm not changing it.

06:31.942 --> 06:33.442
Besides,
I spent all my money.

06:33.560 --> 06:34.643
Then I'll pay for it.

06:34.728 --> 06:37.229
Wow, he must
really hate it.

06:38.449 --> 06:39.815
But you said
it was my room.

06:39.900 --> 06:41.316
Yes, but it's my house.

06:42.453 --> 06:43.869
I can't believe you!

06:43.954 --> 06:45.620
You know what?
I am staying at olive's tonight.

06:45.706 --> 06:46.988
Weren't you going
to do that anyway

06:47.074 --> 06:48.573
because of
the paint fumes?

06:49.076 --> 06:50.625
Yes.

06:50.711 --> 06:51.910
But now I have
a better reason.

06:53.297 --> 06:54.996
And I'm going
to olive's, too,

06:55.082 --> 06:57.582
because I'm supporting
my best friend.

06:58.552 --> 06:59.918
And also 'cause I live there.

07:00.471 --> 07:02.504
♪ ♪

07:03.824 --> 07:06.725
♪

07:06.844 --> 07:08.176
hey, what's taking so long?

07:08.262 --> 07:11.179
-I wanna see tall max.
-Max: He's coming!

07:14.234 --> 07:15.901
What do you think?
Do I look taller?

07:15.986 --> 07:19.237
Taller? Run! It's a giant!

07:20.574 --> 07:22.607
How many of your sneakers
did you have to rip up

07:22.743 --> 07:23.859
to make those things?

07:24.528 --> 07:26.445
All of 'em.
The great part is...

07:26.864 --> 07:28.613
You can't tell!

07:28.749 --> 07:31.166
But it's the hair that
really sells tall.

07:31.285 --> 07:33.585
And I was afraid it
wouldn't look natural.

07:34.087 --> 07:35.754
Between the hair
and the shoes,

07:35.873 --> 07:38.123
no one's gonna
make fun of me now.

07:39.259 --> 07:41.960
(laughing)

07:43.347 --> 07:45.013
hoo, look at you!

07:45.682 --> 07:48.517
You do know Halloween's
not for another six months?

07:49.386 --> 07:51.887
Mom, this is serious.
I'm trying to look taller.

07:51.972 --> 07:53.939
I'm the shortest
kid in my grade.

07:54.041 --> 07:55.891
Pete called him
shortstack.

07:55.976 --> 07:58.026
Oh. I'm sorry.

07:58.145 --> 08:00.111
But, going to school like
that isn't going to help.

08:00.230 --> 08:01.613
Your hair looks ridiculous.

08:01.732 --> 08:03.532
(gasps) ridiculous?

08:03.650 --> 08:06.535
It took me three hours to
get it to look like that!

08:06.653 --> 08:09.688
And two hours to get my hand
unstuck from max's head.

08:11.658 --> 08:13.658
Max, please sit down.

08:16.580 --> 08:18.880
Listen, there's always
gonna be some doofus

08:18.999 --> 08:20.882
who's gonna say
something mean to you.

08:21.001 --> 08:23.301
But who cares?
They don't really know you.

08:23.387 --> 08:26.388
You don't get it.
Every class picture is gonna be,

08:26.507 --> 08:28.139
"short kids in front."

08:28.225 --> 08:29.925
it makes me feel like a loser.

08:30.010 --> 08:32.093
How am I supposed to
survive school like this?

08:32.179 --> 08:33.478
Well, if you wear
those shoes to school,

08:33.597 --> 08:34.763
you won't have to
worry about it.

08:34.848 --> 08:36.648
You'll be in the hospital
before lunch.

08:36.733 --> 08:38.183
I'll be fine.

08:38.685 --> 08:39.484
(thud)

08:40.404 --> 08:42.387
gah! Don't worry!

08:42.489 --> 08:43.989
My hair broke my fall!

08:44.074 --> 08:47.108
♪ ♪

08:48.328 --> 08:49.361
are you ready

08:49.496 --> 08:51.863
for our first official
hang in new syd's room?

08:51.949 --> 08:54.533
I have never been more
excited for anything.

08:54.668 --> 08:57.369
And I don't care what
my dad says. I love it.

09:04.211 --> 09:05.743
Huh.

09:06.346 --> 09:09.047
Olive:
What's wrong? Why'd you say...

09:10.050 --> 09:11.550
Huh.

09:13.220 --> 09:15.804
Is it me, or does
this place look

09:15.889 --> 09:18.356
different than it
did last night?

09:18.442 --> 09:19.391
No...

09:19.526 --> 09:21.359
Well, maybe just a hair.

09:21.445 --> 09:23.228
Not that different's
a bad thing.

09:23.313 --> 09:24.779
No. Of course not.

09:24.865 --> 09:26.565
I said I wanted
something different.

09:26.650 --> 09:29.901
And I think we've hit
that one out of the park.

09:30.571 --> 09:33.154
You know, maybe this room
is just so different

09:33.240 --> 09:35.206
that it's a little uncomfortable
when you first see it.

09:35.292 --> 09:36.658
-Exactly.
-I hate it!

09:36.743 --> 09:38.410
I hate it, too!

09:38.495 --> 09:40.495
So how come we loved it
so much last night?

09:40.581 --> 09:42.464
I don't know.

09:42.583 --> 09:45.300
I guess it's like when
I write a new song I love,

09:45.419 --> 09:47.218
and the next morning,
I get up,

09:47.304 --> 09:50.088
take a fresh look at it,
and it sounds like doo-doo.

09:50.223 --> 09:52.724
Are you saying you think
your new room is doo-doo?

09:53.393 --> 09:55.427
I do... Do.

09:56.563 --> 09:57.979
I guess I was just

09:58.098 --> 10:00.315
trying so hard to
make my room different

10:00.434 --> 10:02.851
that I got carried away.

10:02.936 --> 10:04.769
I should've never
listened to my gut.

10:05.772 --> 10:06.988
We trusted you.

10:07.107 --> 10:08.239
(scary voice):
Sorry, olive.

10:08.325 --> 10:10.358
It knows my name!

10:12.362 --> 10:13.578
So have you
seen syd's room?

10:13.697 --> 10:15.664
Why am I asking you? You'll
probably say something like,

10:15.782 --> 10:16.948
"it's totally on point."

10:17.034 --> 10:18.783
not after hearing you say it.

10:19.836 --> 10:22.787
Between us,
I think it's a hot mess.

10:23.874 --> 10:26.207
Wait, we're actually
on the same page?

10:26.293 --> 10:28.293
So then you agree
she should change it?

10:28.428 --> 10:31.596
-No. What are you, nuts?
-And she's back.

10:32.766 --> 10:35.600
Max, kids make tons of decisions
their parents don't like.

10:35.686 --> 10:38.136
-You gotta pick your battles.
-You picked every battle.

10:38.271 --> 10:40.105
Oh really?
Did you know I was dead set

10:40.223 --> 10:41.773
against you getting
a skateboard?

10:41.892 --> 10:43.808
Really? You never told me.

10:43.944 --> 10:45.694
Yeah. I thought
you'd break your neck.

10:45.812 --> 10:48.279
But I kept it to myself,
and I'm glad I did.

10:48.365 --> 10:50.365
You only chipped three teeth
and cracked a rib.

10:50.701 --> 10:53.151
Yeah. I was good.

10:55.072 --> 10:58.156
Imagine what life would've been
like without your skateboard.

10:59.409 --> 11:00.458
I can't.

11:00.577 --> 11:01.876
So maybe you should
think about it

11:01.962 --> 11:03.495
before you make syd
change something

11:03.630 --> 11:06.131
she really has her heart set on.

11:06.216 --> 11:09.250
♪ ♪

11:12.305 --> 11:15.223
seriously, dude?
You're standing
on a milk crate?

11:15.342 --> 11:18.710
Doesn't feel so good,
does it, little man?

11:19.713 --> 11:22.880
Max, what are you
gonna do at school?
Carry that thing around?

11:22.983 --> 11:25.984
'cause I'd rather be
shortstack than crate boy.

11:26.987 --> 11:29.904
Well, it doesn't matter 'cause
I'm not going back to school.

11:29.990 --> 11:31.940
No way am I gonna be
the shortest kid.

11:32.025 --> 11:34.025
Hey, benny.
How's it going?

11:35.112 --> 11:37.746
Yeah, benny?
How's it going?

11:37.864 --> 11:39.531
Never better, my man.

11:40.083 --> 11:41.666
One fake vomit, please.

11:41.752 --> 11:44.335
Sometimes, you gotta
treat yourself.

11:45.005 --> 11:47.122
Ooh, sorry.
You're a little short.

11:47.207 --> 11:49.791
(gasps) oh wait! I-I didn't
mean it in that way. I just--

11:49.876 --> 11:52.127
it's all good.
I'll just get
some more tickets.

11:52.212 --> 11:54.245
I saw a bunch under
the foosball table.

11:55.015 --> 11:57.966
When you're low to the ground,
you notice those things.

12:01.188 --> 12:03.555
-You know what I'm thinking?
-Never.

12:05.058 --> 12:06.641
I should hang out
with benny more.

12:06.727 --> 12:08.526
We were buds in 2nd grade.

12:08.612 --> 12:10.111
This wouldn't have
anything to do

12:10.230 --> 12:11.863
with benny being shorter
than you, would it?

12:11.948 --> 12:13.865
(scoffs)
of course it does!

12:13.984 --> 12:15.984
Try to keep up, leo.

12:16.703 --> 12:18.870
As long as I'm
standing next to benny,

12:18.955 --> 12:20.371
I won't be the shortest
kid in class.

12:21.374 --> 12:24.375
I don't know, max. I'm not
sure this is the best idea.

12:24.461 --> 12:27.078
On the other hand,
next to your other ideas,

12:27.214 --> 12:28.379
it's genius.

12:28.465 --> 12:30.999
♪ ♪

12:31.084 --> 12:32.467
sydney:
<i> What am I gonna do?</i>

12:32.552 --> 12:34.169
I can't live in here.

12:35.088 --> 12:37.589
Maybe my dad was... Was...

12:37.724 --> 12:41.125
-Right?
-Thanks. My mouth was never
gonna allow me to say that.

12:41.645 --> 12:43.261
Then redo it.
He offered to pay.

12:43.346 --> 12:46.397
No 'cause then every time
he disagrees with me, he'll say,

12:46.483 --> 12:48.433
(imitating):
"remember how I was
right about your room?"

12:49.936 --> 12:51.069
wait!

12:51.154 --> 12:52.904
Why does he ever have
to know you hate it?

12:52.989 --> 12:54.606
He's gonna make you
redo the place anyway.

12:54.691 --> 12:56.474
What are you saying?

12:56.576 --> 12:58.159
Pretend he's making me do it?

12:58.278 --> 13:00.078
I know,
it's pretty devious--

13:00.163 --> 13:01.979
that's why I love it.

13:02.082 --> 13:05.366
I mean, how hard is it to
act like an angry teenager?

13:05.452 --> 13:08.119
Please. It's the role
I was born to play.

13:09.172 --> 13:11.289
Syd, I think we should
discuss your room.

13:11.424 --> 13:13.541
Why? So you can tell me
to change it back?

13:13.627 --> 13:14.876
You're ruining my life.

13:14.961 --> 13:16.845
Actually, I was going to
say that you can keep it.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.963
Why can't you be like other--
what's what?

13:19.966 --> 13:21.499
You were right.
Doesn't matter what I think.

13:21.601 --> 13:23.184
The important thing
is that you love it.

13:24.054 --> 13:26.221
But dad, it's like you said.
It's your house.

13:26.306 --> 13:27.856
But it's your room.
Look, syd,

13:27.941 --> 13:30.892
all I know is if you're happy,
then I'm happy.

13:30.977 --> 13:31.976
Happy?

13:32.779 --> 13:34.179
Oh, you have no idea.

13:34.865 --> 13:36.981
♪ ♪

13:38.585 --> 13:41.653
♪ ♪

13:43.240 --> 13:44.823
hey, syd,
I heard the good news.

13:44.908 --> 13:47.725
Your dad's gonna let you keep
your room the way you want it.

13:47.828 --> 13:50.328
Yeah. How can he be so mean?

13:51.248 --> 13:52.897
Okay, now I'm
officially confused.

13:52.999 --> 13:54.499
I thought you loved this room?

13:54.634 --> 13:56.000
Well, I thought I did, too,

13:56.119 --> 13:58.670
but in the light
of day... Yikes.

14:00.457 --> 14:02.240
So then, why don't you just
tell your dad how you feel?

14:02.342 --> 14:03.875
And let him know he was right?

14:04.010 --> 14:06.461
-You mean the "I-told-you-so's"?
-And don't forget the,

14:06.546 --> 14:09.714
(imitating):
"are you sure?
Haven't we been here before?"

14:09.850 --> 14:12.183
ah, that sounds
like old syd.

14:12.285 --> 14:13.268
What do you mean?

14:13.386 --> 14:14.385
Well, part of growing up

14:14.521 --> 14:16.387
is being able to admit
when you're wrong.

14:17.274 --> 14:18.773
Like this ridiculous outfit.

14:18.892 --> 14:20.225
I mean, what have
I been thinking?

14:20.360 --> 14:21.643
My shoes are killing me.

14:21.728 --> 14:24.279
French women must have
a thing for bunions.

14:24.397 --> 14:26.314
Well then, why are you doing
this whole french thing?

14:26.399 --> 14:27.815
Well, your dad was right.
I was just trying

14:27.901 --> 14:29.484
to keep my vacation going.

14:29.569 --> 14:31.269
I should've just bought
a mona lisa bobblehead

14:31.371 --> 14:33.321
like everyone else.

14:34.040 --> 14:37.108
So I guess new syd is gonna have
to tell her dad he was right.

14:37.827 --> 14:40.662
That is what a mature
woman would do.

14:41.748 --> 14:44.299
Oh, but don't tell your dad why
I dumped the whole french thing.

14:44.417 --> 14:46.751
We can't let him
be right twice.

14:49.472 --> 14:51.723
It's been a blast hanging
out with you again, max.

14:51.808 --> 14:53.675
Right back at you, benny.

14:56.062 --> 14:57.345
Hey. There's tamira.

14:57.430 --> 14:59.898
Wait here. I'm gonna
go ask her out.

14:59.983 --> 15:01.182
Wait.

15:01.268 --> 15:03.067
You're gonna
ask out tamira?

15:03.186 --> 15:05.469
Don't you think
she's a little...

15:05.572 --> 15:07.772
How do I put this...
Out of your reach?

15:08.441 --> 15:09.908
Only one way to find out.

15:17.584 --> 15:20.335
Okay, good news. Tamira
said she'd get back to me.

15:20.453 --> 15:22.287
She needs to see if she
can get out of babysitting.

15:23.123 --> 15:24.672
Right.

15:24.758 --> 15:26.591
Babysitting.

15:27.327 --> 15:29.260
Hey, benny. I got
someone else to babysit.

15:29.379 --> 15:30.962
Cool. I'll meet
you there at 6:00.

15:31.097 --> 15:33.131
Can't wait to mini-golf.

15:34.935 --> 15:36.884
Yup. Mm-hmm.

15:37.887 --> 15:39.187
I can't believe it.

15:39.306 --> 15:40.688
She said yes?

15:40.774 --> 15:43.674
And you invited her to do
something that involves the word

15:43.777 --> 15:45.509
"mini"?

15:45.612 --> 15:48.646
Max, why are you
so surprised?

15:48.732 --> 15:49.897
Because I'm short?

15:50.817 --> 15:53.484
You are? I never noticed.

15:54.821 --> 15:56.537
Max, it's not
about altitude.

15:56.623 --> 15:57.855
It's about attitude.

15:57.958 --> 15:59.824
I don't even think
about how tall I am.

15:59.960 --> 16:01.793
I just think of myself as benny.

16:01.878 --> 16:03.411
That's the way
the world sees me.

16:04.497 --> 16:07.498
Wow. I never thought
of it that way.

16:08.168 --> 16:10.301
Thanks, benny.
B-ball Tuesday?

16:10.387 --> 16:12.420
Well, let's see how
things go with tamira.

16:12.505 --> 16:15.340
I have a feeling I might
be busy for a while.

16:17.310 --> 16:20.544
Whoa, max!
Did you have a growth spurt?

16:20.647 --> 16:22.647
You're taller than me!

16:22.766 --> 16:25.016
Yeah, we're done with that.

16:25.101 --> 16:28.152
Good, 'cause even
I wasn't buying it.

16:28.271 --> 16:29.487
Why the big change?

16:30.156 --> 16:32.357
Leo. Height is
about attitude,

16:32.492 --> 16:35.443
not altitude.
It's how I see myself.

16:35.528 --> 16:38.496
And I gotta be honest,
I like what I see.

16:38.581 --> 16:40.231
Wow! I don't know
if you're taller,

16:40.333 --> 16:42.033
but you definitely
have grown.

16:42.168 --> 16:45.453
Hey. After school,
let's go get some pancakes.

16:45.538 --> 16:47.789
I'm suddenly craving
a short stack.

16:51.544 --> 16:53.678
Dad, I need to talk
to you about my room.

16:53.763 --> 16:54.962
Okay.

16:55.682 --> 16:57.515
-(quietly): You were right.
-I'm sorry, can't hear you.

16:57.634 --> 16:59.300
(mumbling):
You were right.

16:59.386 --> 17:00.852
Syd, I'm sorry.
You're gonna have to speak--

17:00.937 --> 17:02.970
-you were right! I hate it!
-I heard that.

17:03.890 --> 17:05.473
I wanna redo my redo.

17:05.558 --> 17:06.974
And I know what
you're gonna say.

17:07.060 --> 17:10.278
"but you said you liked it."
yeah, but now I don't.

17:10.397 --> 17:14.032
"then I was right?"
yes, so if you wanna say,
"I told you so,"

17:14.150 --> 17:15.566
go ahead.

17:17.787 --> 17:19.603
So when do you
wanna get started?

17:19.939 --> 17:21.939
Wait, that's it?

17:22.042 --> 17:23.458
No "I told you so"?

17:23.543 --> 17:25.910
The dad in my head is
doing a victory dance.

17:26.046 --> 17:28.246
(laughs) why would I do that?

17:28.381 --> 17:30.331
Must've been really hard to
come down here and tell me this,

17:30.417 --> 17:33.251
especially after how hard
you fought for that room.

17:33.336 --> 17:34.919
Honestly, I'm proud of you.

17:35.055 --> 17:36.254
Seriously?

17:36.389 --> 17:38.005
Seriously.

17:38.091 --> 17:39.557
So, you wanna go see
if your old furniture

17:39.642 --> 17:40.758
is at the thrift store?

17:41.227 --> 17:43.928
Nah. I'm just not
that girl anymore.

17:44.564 --> 17:46.564
But I'm not new syd either.

17:47.650 --> 17:50.852
It's scary. I don't
know who I am.

17:51.438 --> 17:52.653
Who says you have to?

17:52.739 --> 17:54.522
You're still growing
into who you're gonna be,

17:54.607 --> 17:57.108
and you can take it
as slow as you want.

17:58.862 --> 18:00.811
Why don't you move into
the girl cave in the basement

18:00.914 --> 18:03.364
until you put together
the room that you love?

18:03.450 --> 18:06.334
You're kidding.
That would be amazing.

18:06.453 --> 18:07.952
Maybe I could move
in there forever...

18:08.872 --> 18:11.789
I'll take this one.
"syd, let's not push it."

18:14.010 --> 18:16.878
dad, thanks for understanding.

18:16.963 --> 18:18.796
You're quite welcome.

18:20.266 --> 18:23.017
So, do you still
wanna hear about camp?

18:23.136 --> 18:25.503
Nah. I mean, I've pretty
much put together--

18:25.605 --> 18:28.106
yes, please! Tell me everything.

18:28.191 --> 18:31.442
♪ ♪

18:32.345 --> 18:35.480
it took me a while to
get it right, but...

18:36.116 --> 18:37.782
<i> Voilà!</i>

18:37.901 --> 18:40.701
Oh, noodle, it's perfect!

18:40.820 --> 18:43.738
The colors,
the texture, the...

18:43.823 --> 18:45.706
<i> -Je ne sais quoi.</i>
-Mom!

18:45.825 --> 18:47.792
What? She said<i> voilà.</i>

18:48.995 --> 18:52.130
I love the esperanza
spalding poster!

18:52.215 --> 18:54.632
Yep. She's just the coolest.

18:54.717 --> 18:56.551
And my own personal hero.

18:56.669 --> 18:58.169
Not that I'm gushing.

18:59.305 --> 19:00.588
Dad, what do you think about it?

19:00.673 --> 19:02.507
What do I think?

19:02.642 --> 19:04.475
I think it's fantastic.

19:04.561 --> 19:07.478
Aw, and I love this old
picture of you and your mom.

19:09.983 --> 19:11.382
Are these your old
ballet slippers?

19:11.818 --> 19:14.018
-Yep.
-I love it all, syd.

19:15.188 --> 19:17.071
Really? There's gotta be
something in this room

19:17.190 --> 19:18.489
that isn't dad-approved.

19:18.575 --> 19:20.691
Well, honestly, I don't get

19:20.827 --> 19:22.243
that thing
over there.

19:22.328 --> 19:24.996
Oh, thank goodness.

19:25.498 --> 19:27.064
Noodle, why don't
we leave you alone

19:27.167 --> 19:29.250
so you can enjoy your room?

19:29.369 --> 19:30.334
Thanks, grandma.

19:30.420 --> 19:32.253
Oh really? I was hoping
syd and I could hang,

19:32.338 --> 19:34.088
maybe spill some tea.

19:34.874 --> 19:37.208
Okay. There's another phrase
I'll never use again.

19:39.963 --> 19:43.714
(sighs) well, gut, I think
we did a pretty good job.

19:44.684 --> 19:47.518
(scary voice):
Thanks. When's dinner?

19:47.604 --> 19:50.888
♪ ♪

19:51.057 --> 19:53.707
man:
<i> Oh yeah.</i>
